@startuml
title Login, Access, Refresh Rotation, and Session Revocation

actor User
participant "App Frontend/API" as APP
participant "Identity Service (AuthN)" as IDN
database "Session Store" as SESS
participant "Resource API\n(Spring Resource Server)" as API

== Login ==
User -> APP: Submit email/password
APP -> IDN: POST /identity/v1/login
IDN -> SESS: Create session + store refresh token hash (ACTIVE)
IDN --> APP: access_token(JWT, short TTL) + refresh_token
APP --> User: Session established

== Access ==
User -> APP: Request protected resource
APP -> API: GET /api/... with Bearer access_token
API -> API: Validate JWT (signature, iss, aud, exp)
API -> API: @PreAuthorize checks (scope/claims)
API --> APP: 200 OK
APP --> User: Data

APP -> IDN: GET /identity/v1/session (Bearer access_token)
IDN -> SESS: Resolve sid claim to session state
IDN --> APP: session_id + status + expiry context

== Refresh ==
User -> APP: Access token expired
APP -> IDN: POST /identity/v1/refresh (refresh_token)
IDN -> SESS: Verify refresh hash + ACTIVE + not expired + not revoked
IDN -> SESS: Mark old refresh token ROTATED; insert new ACTIVE token
IDN --> APP: New access_token + new refresh_token
APP --> User: Continue without re-login

== Reuse Detection ==
APP -> IDN: POST /identity/v1/refresh (previous rotated token)
IDN -> SESS: Detect ROTATED token reuse
IDN -> SESS: Revoke session + revoke token family
IDN --> APP: 401 Unauthorized

== Logout ==
User -> APP: Logout
APP -> IDN: POST /identity/v1/logout (latest refresh token)
IDN -> SESS: Revoke session + revoke token family
IDN --> APP: 204 No Content

@enduml
